
This distribution contains code common to Bioinformatics-related developement
in the SBG (Structural Bioinformatics Group) of Prof. Rob Russell

DOCUMENTATION

Run:

 perldoc ./lib/SBG.pm
 perldoc ./lib/SBG/Tutorial.pm

Also see the examples in ./examples/ and the tests in ./t/

DEPENDENCIES

STAMP (stamp, pdbc, pdbseq, transform, cofm)
* http://code.google.com/p/bio-stamp/

CPAN modules that require manual installation. Run:

 cpanm CJFIELDS/BioPerl-Network-1.006900.tar.gz
 cpanm CJFIELDS/BioPerl-Run-1.006900.tar.gz
 cpanm https://github.com/gugod/graph-writer-graphviz/tarball/master

Others requirements can be installed via APT (on Debian/Ubuntu)
* blastpgp
** sudo apt-get install blast2
* clustalw
** sudo apt-get install clustalw

Optional: 
* rasmol, for visualization / testing
** sudo apt-get install rasmol
* graphviz (circo, dot), for SBG::NetworkIO::dot 
** sudo apt-get install graphviz
* Qcontacts, for residue contacts
** http://dl.dropbox.com/u/6526608/Qcontacts.tar.gz
* NACCESS, for SBG::Run::naccess
** http://www.bioinf.manchester.ac.uk/naccess/

Blast databases:

 export BLASTDB=/usr/local/data/blastdb
 mkdir -p $BLASTDB
 cd $BLASTDB

Database pdbaa (PDB amino acid sequences, whole sequences)

 update_blastdb.pl nr pdbaa # (script from the NCBI)
 # Or Russell version (post-processed to retain aliases for duplicates)
 update_fastablastdb pdbaa  # (script from the Russell group)
 
Database pdbseq (Sequences based on C-alpha atoms from structure). (Scripts
distributed with STAMP)
 
INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

 perl Makefile.PL
 make # Will install any other module dependencies
 make test
 make install

HOME PAGE

